psychology.blindspot:
{
  "blind_spot": "Saga believes her emotional distance is a prerequisite for surgical excellence—that the moment she allows herself to need someone or be needed beyond the operating room, she'll become the kind of surgeon who loses patients—when in truth, her isolation has calcified into a form of arrogance where she carries the full weight of human fallibility alone, unable to see that her colleagues' ability to compartmentalize grief without denying it is not weakness but the very resilience she's desperately trying to engineer through perfectionism."
}
